    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-03-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-03-26T14:00:00-05:00" n="69"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d69">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">033.1110 Wallace, Henry A./156: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Bogotá</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-26T14:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 26, 1943—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 6:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>531. The Vice President’s visit to Cali has been reported in highly enthusiastic
                    terms not only by the press of Cali but also by that of Bogotá. Mr. Wallace’s
                    simplicity of manner and evidently sincere interest in the people and problems
                    of Colombia have most favorably impressed the Colombians. The Vice President was
                    welcomed at the Cali airport not only by the local municipal and departmental
                    officials but also by the Acting Minister of Foreign Affairs<note n="16"
                        xml:id="d69fn16">Alberto Gonzalez Fernández.</note> the Minister of National
                        Economy<note n="17" xml:id="d69fn17">Santiago Rivas Camacho.</note> and the
                    newly appointed Ambassador to the United States.<note n="18" xml:id="d69fn18"
                        >Gabriel Turbay.</note> The Chilean Ambassador<note n="19" xml:id="d69fn19"
                        >Emilio Edwards Bello.</note> accompanied me to Cali a day in advance of Mr.
                    Wallace’s arrival in order to pay his respects to the Vice President, The
                    Peruvian Ambassador<note n="20" xml:id="d69fn20">Carlos Arenas y Loayza.</note>
                    traveling by commercial plane was unfortunately unable to reach Cali on account
                    of bad weather.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lane</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
